      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLITZ (1) was safely held last time finishing a 9 length sixth at this track (23.47) but back to the scene of her latest victory. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Better than last start and worth following up. BETH DUTTON (2) started big odds last time but hit the ground running with a slick early split, giving a sight but fading out of it to finish fourth (23.33) at this track over 401m. Speedy beginner who should be prominent early on from an inside box. One of the better hopes. ALL FOR IRISH (7) had the drop on the lead from the rails draw last start but could only manage second, beaten 2.25 lengths (18.67) at this track in a Mix 3/4 over 320m. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Bold showing expected. KELLY BONKERS (4) can play a role in the finish without surprising.",
